trend_summary: Imagery reveals a leafy suburb that slowly intensifies. Cul-de-sac subdivisions and new commercial blocks fill gaps, especially near the former airfield, parts of which convert to sports and mixed use. Main roads widen, but maturing street trees and river-edge conservation enlarge canopy cover. Built footprint rises modestly while green space stays significant.
notable_changes: Portions of the south-eastern runway area replaced by sports fields and mixed-use buildings.
New residential cul-de-sac streets appear in the north-west and central sectors.
Expansion of commercial/industrial blocks and parking near the former airfield.
Widening and extension of the main north-south arterial road.
Overall tree canopy cover increases along riverbanks and residential streets.
